00:00.000 --> 00:03.259
Here's a quick overview of the invoicing process as a whole.

00:03.655 --> 00:06.723
The OPs personnel, requests for a ticket from the airlines. 

00:07.017 --> 00:11.363
All the while, he or she, would input all the necessary data into iGATOR. 

00:12.138 --> 00:15.710
In turn, a TOR is created which also simultaneously creates 

00:15.710 --> 00:20.098
an exact copy in the form of a Purchase Order, which goes directly into PRISM. 

00:20.689 --> 00:24.539
All the while, the airlines will issue an invoice and send it over to AIS. 

00:24.909 --> 00:28.178
AIS will then check and verify the invoice information 

00:28.178 --> 00:30.178
with the PO information in PRISM. 

00:30.700 --> 00:33.158
Once verified, the invoice will be processed.

00:33.464 --> 00:36.711
After which, AIS will request Treasury to continue 

00:36.711 --> 00:38.711
with the remittance to the Airlines Partners. 

00:39.419 --> 00:41.419
This completes the invoicing process.

